==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adipocere
<hw>Ad"i*po*cere`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adeps</ets>, <ets>adipis</ets>, fat + <ets>cera</ets> wax: cf. F.
<ets>adipocere</ets>.]</ety> <def>A soft, unctuous, or waxy substance,
of a light brown color, into which the fat and muscle tissue of dead
bodies sometimes are converted, by long immersion in water or by burial
in moist places. It is a result of fatty degeneration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adipoceriform</ent>⟦br⟧
